INSERT INTO `broadcast_text` (`Text`, `Text1`, `ID`, `LanguageID`, `ConditionID`, `EmotesID`, `Flags`, `ChatBubbleDurationMs`, `VoiceOverPriorityID`, `SoundKitID1`, `SoundKitID2`, `EmoteID1`, `EmoteID2`, `EmoteID3`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
('', 'Hmmmmm... Da farthest norf has to be Northrend, right? Unco Benny used to tell me about a small island even more norf than the main continent! Maybe there\'s a Tuskarr \"watcher\" somewhere on tat island. And if so...\n\n<Maru seems to be concentrating really hard.>\n\nDa sun sets to the west...\nFacing west and... <mumble> right shoulder... is norf...\n\nThis one sure takes a lot of finking!', 276397, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Aye! I\'m not entirely sure where or what it is though.\n\nI asked him about it once, and he only chuckled and said, \"In the farthest north, start yer thinkin\' at the foot of the Lone Watcher. Then follow twelve as the sun sets, and eight over his left shoulder.\"\n\n<Bonenose shrugs.>\n\nI don\'t have a clue, but that\'s all I have for ya, I\'m afraid.', '', 274457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Looks like all you\'re missing now is the secret ingredient.', '', 274455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it hummock jaypops, which decoded to highland crawdaddies.\n\nI bet tat\'s furious crawdads! But where could you find those?', 274222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it sholazar roils, which decoded to sholazar nettles.\n\nTat could refer to nettlefish in da Sholazar Basin.', 274220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it bumper flower brinestock, which decoded to giant growth fish.\n\nTat might be a deviate fish. It\'s one of the fings you need to make an elixir of giant growth, I fink.', 274219, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it ghost breath mouser brine, which decoded to deadwind catfish.\n\nTat sounds like bloodfin catfish to me. They\'re all over Deadwind Pass.', 274218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it koatini\'s grease, which decoded to koatini\'s oil.\n\nI fink tat\'s aromatic fish oil! You can extract it yourself, but Koatini is the only person I know who sells it.', 274217, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it blaze gasping ice pods, which decoded to fire breathing chili sacs.\n\nTat might be small flame sacs, used to make dragonbreath chili.', 274216, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it daffy juice berries, which decoded to banana rum berries.\n\nTat sounds like witchberries! Those are used to make banana-infused rum, from what I\'ve heard.', 274215, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Hmm. He called it shadow leaf, which decoded to rogue\'s thistle.\n\nTat sounds a lot like swiftthistle to me. Rogues use tat all the time to make thistle tea!', 274214, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Oooo! Secret recipes and encrypted ingredient lists? Which one do you need help wiff?', 274203, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('It\'s true, I hide here when the faire is out of town. There\'s just something wonderful about this place.\n\nCare to battle?', '', 273890, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Ohh, this feather definitely came from somewhere freezing.\n\nAnd tat smell... What cold place would have a combination of all of these smells? Maybe somewhere wiff a ship?', 271812, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Tat feather looks plucked on purpose...\n\nMaybe the number of tiny feathers left can help? Look reeaally closely at the feathers. I bet da finking cap can help!\n\nI fink the left number will be negative and the right number will be positive. Make sure you start from where you found the previous clue! You saw a bunch of scrolls near it, right?', 271811, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Eww, what\'s tat dripping off da feather?\n\nLooks like it was in a battle. Hmm... Wasn\'t there a big battle at a city in Draenor?', 271807, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Arakkoa? I heard they would fly around the Spires of Arak.\n\nTry looking in high places there wiff your idol!', 271800, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('The clue is this: The winds whisper secrets, high above the ground. Seek the feather where the Arakkoa once soared.', '', 271799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Precisely! Well... sort of.\n\nI\'ve repurposed an old damaged databank we used in our consoles to send and receive information to and from the Archive. \n\nThis one happened to have an intact memory core, so I synced it up with a projection crystal, modified its response protocols and bypassed as many encrypted override commands as I--well, I won\'t bore you with all of the technical detail.\n\nThe haulbot is... well, a haulbot. It just holds the emitter, but I think it brings it all together nicely, don\'t you?', '', 270355, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Conversation initi-- I mean, greetings fellow awakened!\n\nI am Kromleg, former machinist and... well, I\'m still a machinist in fact. \n\nDawn said we can be whoever we want, but... I quite liked who I was. I didn\'t mind my job. So, I\'m sticking to it!\n\nIn the days after I awoke, I noticed many earthen had questions and uncertainties. Some remembered who they were while others had trouble piecing the fragments together--stasis is hard on the cognitive matrix.\n\nIn a previous cycle, I might have disapproved of those uncertainties. But now I feel inspired to help quell those questions with answers, rather than dismissals.', '', 270354, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Upon the completion of the Stonevault\'s construction, the Caretakers were designated as the custodians and stewards of the earthen life cycle. \n\nWithin the Hall of Awakening, Caretakers tend to the earthen emerging from stasis, while others would oversee and monitor those stored within the expansive halls of the Stonevault.\n\nAs active earthen drew closer to stasis-lock, Caretakers were assigned to the field to guide and, in some cases, transport them to the Stonevault to recharge their cycle anew. \n\nAs all designations are expected to adhere to the Stasis and Awakening Protocol, Caretakers are assigned to all branches of earthen society including the Stormriders, the Stonebound, and the Machine Speakers.', '', 270320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Before the Archive within Dornogal was initialized, the Archivists, sometimes referred to as Compilers, were assigned the task of recording all incident reports, project interruptions, or general site related updates.\n\nUpon the completion of the Archive within Dornogal, the Archivists were assigned the role of organizing the information extracted from earthen memory gems.\n\nArchivists are assigned to key locations around Sector AR-938 to maintain records of ongoing events. These locations included Dornogal, the Ringing Deeps, the Stormperch, and the Stonevault.\n\nAdditional information on the Archivists and the Archive has been encrypted under Protocol 141-LAK-1R1.', '', 270319, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('The Machine Speakers are assigned to maintain and expand the many vaults and machines hidden within Sector AR-938. \n\nPrimarily found within the Ringing Deeps and along the Coreway, the Machine Speakers use their prowess and mastery over the ancient machines to govern the subterranean work sites and workers within. \n\nThis designation included the ranks of worker, foreman, machinist, Speaker, and High Speaker. With the High Speaker serving on the Dornogal Council as the representative of this designation, it was by his directive that all Machine Speakers and workers carried out their duty with strict adherence.\n\nMachine Speakers are found within the Earthenworks, the Waterworks, the Golemworks and the Stonevault.', '', 270318, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Operational support units worked in the subterranean work sites within Sector AR-938. \n\nThese workers were dedicated to the installation and maintenance of the many machines and vaults within and below the Ringing Deeps.\n\nAt the direction of the Machine Speakers, these units served as work hands, laborers, smiths and machine operators. \n\nMachinists of the Deeps were deployed to key sites such as Taelloch, Gundargaz, Ironhaul Station and the Earthenworks facility.', '', 270314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('A tragic end.', '', 269959, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 262747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('You stand in the presence of a wondrous machine, outlander. \n\nTake a moment to appreciate its grandeur.', 'You stand in the presence of a wondrous machine, outlander. \n\nTake a moment to appreciate its grandeur.', 268859, 0, 126070, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('The Caretakers welcome you in these sacred halls, outlander. Do tread lightly.', 'The Caretakers welcome you in these sacred halls, outlander. Do tread lightly.', 268858, 0, 126070, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Tread gently in these halls, outlander. There are many more earthen yet to awaken.', 'Tread gently in these halls, outlander. There are many more earthen yet to awaken.', 268856, 0, 126070, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'I\'m starting to understand why we were met with some distrustful gazes when we first arrived.\n\nThe tauren tell me of their history with our fleshy descendants and how they tore through their land in search of treasure and secrets--secrets pertaining to my kin, no less.. \n\n<Hekgarda exhales softly as she shakes her head.>\n\nEven the most ambitious of the Stonebound knew that when the earth rumbled and quaked, its voice must be heard, and its might respected, lest we paid the price for angering it.\n\nThere is a mighty reverence for the land here. Perhaps others Stonebound will visit it one day.', 268664, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'The only form of leisure I knew as a Peacekeeper was spending time in the firebaths. I finally take the opportunity to leave the isle and what do I do? Find a place to soak!\n\nThe salt deposits in these canyons make for some mineral rich water basins! It sort of reminds me of Boulder Springs... but maybe I\'m a little home sick.', 268303, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('<The weave-rat quakes with uncertainty as it stares into the abyss. It provides you a missive with a single instruction: find and retrieve a shipping manifest from the Sureki forces working in the Maddening Deep.>', '<The weave-rat quakes with uncertainty as it stares into the abyss. It provides you a missive with a single instruction: find and retrieve a shipping manifest from the Sureki forces working in the Maddening Deep.>', 266997, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('<You peer into the Heart of Azeroth and feel as if you\'re being pulled into the very depths of existence itself. Everything seems to stop. The lights of the world as you know it seems to cease to be as you gaze deeper into the amulet.\n\nIn the darkness of the world one thing becomes clear... \n\nIt\'s time to go do another task that a dwarf encased in diamond claiming to be Magni is asking you to do.>', '', 266648, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('You should have run.', '', 266298, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 253401, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('<The weave-rat eyes you curiously. Upon its leg is a missive detailing the movements of illicit Sureki contraband. Perhaps there is an opportunity to be found here.>', '<The weave-rat eyes you curiously. Upon its leg is a missive detailing the movements of illicit Sureki contraband. Perhaps there is an opportunity to be found here.>', 264770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Venomancy is an ancient practice in our empire. Like all ancient practices, it fosters secrecy--and the Vizier does not tolerate any secrecy but his own.\n\nHis eminence would like their threat to be mitigated. You have the benefit of presumed idiocy among the Sureki. We do not.\n\nVenture to their enclave in the Skeins and destroy any alchemical flasks the venomancers have left about.', 'Venomancy is an ancient practice in our empire. Like all ancient practices, it fosters secrecy--and the Vizier does not tolerate any secrecy but his own.\n\nHis eminence would like their threat to be mitigated. You have the benefit of presumed idiocy among the Sureki. We do not.\n\nVenture to their enclave in the Skeins and destroy any alchemical flasks the venomancers have left about.', 264764, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('His Eminence is, I fear, running short on a vital component of his patented sleeping draught. There are a number of citizens who struggle to rest without it. It may seem a small gesture, but the Vizier considers the well-being of the citizenry to be of paramount importance.\n\nLuckily, you can help with that. The snails here in the gorge feast upon a certain herb known to induce drowsiness. As a result, their antennae prove potent reagents. Gather some, won\'t you?', 'His Eminence is, I fear, running short on a vital component of his patented sleeping draught. There are a number of citizens who struggle to rest without it. It may seem a small gesture, but the Vizier considers the well-being of the citizenry to be of paramount importance.\n\nLuckily, you can help with that. The snails here in the gorge feast upon a certain herb known to induce drowsiness. As a result, their antennae prove potent reagents. Gather some, won\'t you?', 264760, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('The Flame burns bright with the faith of the Arathi. But it takes a true champion to wield it with such conviction.', '', 264670, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 252031, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('The Sacred Flame is powerful. Even those outside our faith can wield it through the use of holy oil.', '', 264669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 252030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Not so strong without candle, are they?', 264487, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 250898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'It\'s time! Go take candle!', 264486, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 4, 0, 250897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'To me!', 264069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 251920, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('That\'s that then. Can you imagine what those multi-limbed freaks would\'ve done with even a drop of Cinderbrew?', '', 263912, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 251944, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Those confounded nerubians are still lurking around my meadery! Clear them out before they steal my cinderbrew!', '', 263911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 251943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('', 'Takin\' a break? My kindred spirit. You\'re more than welcome to join us for a sit \'n think.', 261222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Help save Azeroth, of course! Why, I\'m one of its greatest champions. I\'ve traveled the world and different planes of existence, but now I\'m stuck in this cave.\n\nCan we get moving?', '', 258279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 584, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Of course I can talk. You talk, why can\'t I talk? Got more silly questions?', '', 258277, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534),
('Log Entry: Pulsating Seeds \n\nMalygos seemed fascinated by the fact that these seeds have a defense mechanism that cause them to detonate when handled without due care. I filed them away for safe keeping. I suspect nurturing them to life would be a... poor decision.', 'Log Entry: Pulsating Seeds \n\nMalygos seemed fascinated by the fact that these seeds have a defense mechanism that cause them to detonate when handled without due care. I filed them away for safe keeping. I suspect nurturing them to life would be a... poor decision.', 231524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57534);
